<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>I've tested it including L18 Pal vs L16 Ranger</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:29 p.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> I've tested it including L18 Pal vs L16 Ranger<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=395" TARGET=_self>yea  good ideas for resist, atk and dam...</A> (Tempra[CC])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>I have test results for a L18 Paladin vs L16 Ranger. The Ranger had equal or better ATK and DAM numbers due to buffing, and a higher AC. The Ranger also had dual attack and equal or better weapons than the Paladin. The Paladin beat the crap out of the Ranger and forced the Ranger to zone near death and out of mana while the Paladin was at full mana and not significantly hurt. The Paladin did not even use Lay Hands and the Ranger used good tactics (superior to the Paladin). The main difference was the levels.
<P>&gt; should be based on the numbers... if i'm lvl 50 and i got 30
<BR>&gt; resist i should resist the same amount of times as anyone with
<BR>&gt; 30 resist no more or less because of my level. same with attack
<BR>&gt; and defense, if you got the same numbers between the levels you
<BR>&gt; should have the same oppurtunity to hit each other and for you
<BR>&gt; to block. This might be the case... when i was fighting my
<BR>&gt; friend who was a cleric and i being a druid we were pretty equal
<BR>&gt; when he fought me at a lower lvl. Since his attack and defense
<BR>&gt; were both higher then me he was better then me at melee, but in
<BR>&gt; magic it didnt even compare. Melee might be fine the way it
<BR>&gt; is... havent tried if it is level based or number based.
<P>&gt; This is the #1 reason why PvP will or won't work in Everquest.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
